Note: File I/O Functions for Audio Export
Process called "write_audio_samples_to_file" that takes path as String and samples as List[AudioSample] returns Boolean:
    Note: Write audio samples to file with format detection from extension
    Try:
        Let format be detect_format_from_path with path as path
        Let writer be create_audio_writer with path as path and format as format
        Let success be write_samples_to_writer with writer as writer and samples as samples
        Let close_success be close_audio_writer with writer as writer
        Return success and close_success
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "detect_format_from_path" that takes path as String returns AudioFormat:
    Note: Detect audio format from file extension
    Let extension be get_file_extension with path as path
    If extension is equal to "wav":
        Return WAV
    Otherwise if extension is equal to "flac":
        Return FLAC
    Otherwise if extension is equal to "mp3":
        Return MP3
    Otherwise if extension is equal to "aiff":
        Return AIFF
    Otherwise if extension is equal to "ogg":
        Return OGG_VORBIS
    Otherwise:
        Return WAV  Note: Default to WAV format

Process called "create_audio_writer" that takes path as String and format as AudioFormat returns AudioWriter:
    Note: Create audio writer for specific format with proper headers and encoding
    Try:
        Return system_call_create_audio_writer with path as path and format as format
    Catch error:
        Return AudioWriter with:
            format as format
            sample_format as PCM_16
            sample_rate as 44100
            channels as 2
            file_path as path
            metadata as dictionary containing
            write_buffer as list containing
            bytes_written as 0
            is_open as false

Process called "write_samples_to_writer" that takes writer as AudioWriter and samples as List[AudioSample] returns Boolean:
    Note: Write audio samples to writer with proper format encoding
    Try:
        Return system_call_write_audio_samples with writer as writer and samples as samples
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "close_audio_writer" that takes writer as AudioWriter returns Boolean:
    Note: Close audio writer and finalize file with proper headers and metadata
    Try:
        Return system_call_close_audio_writer with writer as writer
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "get_file_extension" that takes path as String returns String:
    Note: Extract file extension from path
    Let path_length be length of path
    For i from path_length minus 1 down to 0:
        If character at index i in path is equal to ".":
            Return substring of path from index i plus 1
    Return ""  Note: No extension found

Note: Production audio format types for streaming and processing
Type SampleFormat is:
    | PCM_8
    | PCM_16
    | PCM_24
    | PCM_32
    | FLOAT_32
    | FLOAT_64

Type AudioSample is Float

Type called "AudioBuffer":
    samples as List[AudioSample]
    channels as Integer
    sample_rate as Integer
    length as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "EffectChain":
    effects as List[Any]
    bypass_all as Boolean
    input_gain as Float
    output_gain as Float
    parallel_processing as Boolean

Type ProcessingResult is:
    | ProcessingSuccess with buffer as AudioBuffer
    | ProcessingError with message as String and code as String

Process called "create_audio_buffer" that takes channels as Integer and sample_rate as Integer and length as Integer returns AudioBuffer:
    Let samples be list containing
    For i from 0 to channels times length minus 1:
        Add 0.0 to samples
    Return AudioBuffer with:
        samples as samples
        channels as channels
        sample_rate as sample_rate
        length as length
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "get_channel_samples" that takes buffer as AudioBuffer and channel as Integer returns List[AudioSample]:
    Let channel_samples be list containing
    Let channels be buffer["channels"]
    Let length be buffer["length"]
    For i from 0 to length minus 1:
        Let sample_index be i times channels plus channel
        Add buffer["samples"] at index sample_index to channel_samples
    Return channel_samples

Process called "set_channel_samples" that takes buffer as AudioBuffer and channel as Integer and samples as List[AudioSample] returns AudioBuffer:
    Let channels be buffer["channels"]
    Let length be buffer["length"]
    For i from 0 to length minus 1:
        If i is less than length of samples:
            Let sample_index be i times channels plus channel
            Set buffer["samples"] at index sample_index to samples at index i
    Return buffer

Process called "process_effect_chain" that takes chain as EffectChain and buffer as AudioBuffer returns ProcessingResult:
    Note: Simplified effect chain processing
    Return ProcessingSuccess with buffer as buffer